Hey all, new developer here trying to follow the UI Extensions Quickstart <https://developers.HubSpot.com/docs/platform/ui-extensions-quickstart|guide> — I got to the end of step 2, but when I tried to run `hs project upload`  I got an error saying that my `example-card.json`  file “doesn’t match the associated scheme.” I’ve checked against the example files in the documentation <https://developers.HubSpot.com/docs/platform/create-ui-extensions|here>, and it looks like it matches. Based on the errors, though, it looks like it wants something in this structure in the “data” object.
```"fetch": {
      "targetFunction": "string",
      "objectTypes": [{
        "name": "string",
        "propertiesToSend": ["string"]
      }]
    }```
Once I made it fit that schema, I was able to upload the project and begin local dev, but the card itself always errors on the CRM record. Has anyone come across this before/any idea where to find documentation on this? Thanks in advance :pray:
